18/03/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu said on Wednesday (March 17th) that the downsizing of KFOR troops demonstrates improved security in the young country.
Sejdiu briefed ambassadors of NATO member-states in Brussels about Kosovo's achievements as an independent state, adding that for the first time since it declared independence in February 2008, Kosovo has managed to maintain its overall stability.
(TV 21, RTK, Kohavision, Arta TV - 17/03/10)
